<subSubSection pageId="5" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[706,1194,194,1357]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,812,964,985]" pageId="5">Biology.</emphasis>
Given the collection methods (see species account below), it is likely that members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lord and Ivie" authorityYear="2016" box="[741,866,1018,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Globotrichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[741,866,1018,1039]" italics="true" pageId="5">Globotrichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are generalist detritovores and fungivores like many other members of the soildwelling 
<taxonomicName box="[797,897,1071,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synchitini">Synchitini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[706,1194,194,1357]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,1097,1118]" pageId="5">Comments.</emphasis>
Ten of the 14 known specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lord and Ivie" authorityYear="2016" box="[735,860,1124,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Globotrichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,860,1124,1145]" italics="true" pageId="5">Globotrichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are included in the 
<typeStatus box="[1061,1102,1124,1145]" pageId="5">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lord and Ivie" authorityYear="2016" box="[706,790,1151,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Globotrichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harti">
<emphasis box="[706,790,1151,1172]" italics="true" pageId="5">G. harti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the 
<typeStatus box="[908,949,1151,1172]" pageId="5">type</typeStatus>
series limited to those specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[863,965,1177,1198]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1014,1091,1177,1198]" name="Panama" pageId="5">Panama</collectingCountry>
. The other specimens, from Amazonian 
<collectingCountry box="[983,1051,1204,1225]" name="Bolivia" pageId="5">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[744,803,1230,1251]" name="Brazil" pageId="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, probably represent different species, but insufficient material is available for description at this time. It is hoped more material is identified from unsorted material after this paper makes the identity known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
